    <section class="T__section background">
        <h1 class="blue">「 INCREASING REFUGEES 」</h1>
        <div class="T__wrap">
            <div class="layout-1">
                <img src="images/work4/earth.png" alt="Earth">
                <p>According to the data collected from UNHCR (United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees) in 2015, there are 595,000,00 people destitute and homeless all around the word, the number is nearly doubled when it’s compared to the number ten years ago. And 195,000,00 of them are refugees.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <h2>CAUSES</h2>
        <div class="T__wrap">
            <div class="layout-2">
                <div>
                    <h3>Mind Map</h3>
                    <p>On one hand, the problem is mainly caused by war refugees. The chaos and turbulence caused by war as well as ISIS increasingly fuel the issue. <br></p>
                    <img src="images/work4/causes1.jpg" alt="IMG">
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3>Global Polarization</h3>
                    <p>On the other hand, it was also because of polarization during globalization. For the people from some relatively backward economy, Northern and Western Europe would be the solid choice for them.</p>
                    <img src="images/work4/causes2.jpg" alt="IMG">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2>SEVERE SITUATION</h2>
        <div class="T__wrap">
            <div class="layout-3">
                <p>In 2014, refugee number grow fastest in Europe, nearly 220,000 refugees went across Mediterranean and reached Europe. Sorry to say, 2850 people died or missed during the journey.</p>
                <img src="images/work4/problem.jpg" alt="IMG">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="T__wrap">
            <img class="T__wrap-bg" src="images/work4/problem2.jpg" alt="IMG">
        </div>
        <div class="T__wrap">
            <div class="layout-4">
                <p>Turkey contains the largest number of refugees in the world.</p>
                <p>Lebanon contains the highest proportion of the world's refugees. Over 21% of the total population.</p>
                <p>The largest number of refugees in the world: Syria,  Afghanistan and Somali.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="T__wrap">
            <p>The report also shows that more than half of the refugees are under the age of 18, of which only about half of the children have the opportunity to receive primary education, and ultimately only 1% of them could enter college.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="T__section background">
        <h1 class="blue">「 MOUNTAINS of DERELIC 」</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">/The resort is becomeing a garbage dump</div>

        <div class="T__wrap">
            <div class="layout-5">
                <img src="images/work4/derelic.jpg" alt="IMG">
                <p>According to the report from Daily Mail, countless refugess would struggle to make it to Lesbos by boat before going to Greece.  After arival, they will take off their life vests and throw away near Molyvos. Now, there has been an area of more than 40,000 square meters, up to 5 meters of life jackets. <br><br>
                Aerial photographs show that the Greek tourist resort is becoming a garbage dump.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
